#: ../../06_childcare.md:9
msgid ""
"Link it to sponsorships, or university partners, or make part of the "
"registration fee from all attendees go towards providing childcare support "
"as service."
msgstr ""

#: ../../06_childcare.md:10
msgid ""
"Add an option to the registration, e.g.: &quot;Donate $20 to help with "
"childcare costs.&quot;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../06_childcare.md:11
msgid ""
"Collect the data on the registration form. How many people would make use of"
" childcare services or grants?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../06_childcare.md:12
msgid ""
"In general, the two major options are either to 1) award childcare grants "
"(people decide how to spend it, e.g. on their home babysitter) or 2) provide"
" on-site services."
msgstr ""

#: ../../06_childcare.md:14
msgid "Grants"
msgstr ""

#: ../../06_childcare.md:16
msgid ""
"Based on our research, grants to cover childcare costs seem to be more "
"popular with attendees. (On-site childcare services can be costly for "
"attendees because of additional travel costs for bringing children along.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../06_childcare.md:17
msgid ""
"You might survey your participants to determine their preference for grants "
"vs. on-site childcare services."
msgstr ""

#: ../../06_childcare.md:18
msgid ""
"Be sure to consider issues like whether grant recipients will need to submit"
" an invoice or receipt from someone (the childcare provider) with a Tax ID."
msgstr ""

